\pard\f0\fs28 Sect. GLAUCORESEDA DC. Perennials. Leaves entire, with small whitish teeth near the base. Sepals 6; petals white or whitish, the limb cuneate; the two upper 3- or 5-lobed; the two laterals narrower, entire to 3-lobed; the two lower entire or 2-lobed; claw distinct in upper petals. Filaments persistent. Carpels 4. Capsule wider than long.
