\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. R. glauca} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 449 (1753). Stems 10-40 cm, numerous, with short branches. Leaves 15-60 × 1-2 mm, linear, with 0-2 pairs of teeth, glaucous. Bracts 1-3 mm; pedicels 1·5-2·5 mm. Sepals 2 mm; petals 3·5-5 mm, with the limbs of the upper ones wide, 3-lobed to 1/3 of their length, the lobes toothed. Capsule 3-4 × 4-5 mm. 2n = 28.{\i  Alpine and subalpine pastures, rocks and screes. • E. & C. Pyrenees, Cordillera Cantabrica.} Ga Hs.
\par

