\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. R. complicata} Bory, {\i Ann. Gen. Sci. Phys.} ({\i Bruxelles}) {\b 3}: 13 (1820). Like {\b 2} but stems 40-70 cm; stems and branches arcuate-ascending; leaves 15-25 × 1-2·5 mm; bracts 0·5 mm; sepals 1-1·5 mm; petals 2-3 mm, the upper with (3-)5 deeper and narrower lobes; capsule 1·5-3 × 2-3·5 mm, subsessile. 2n = 28.{\i  Montane pastures and damp, gravelly places. • S. Spain} ({\i Sierra Nevada}). Hs.
\par

