\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. R. decursiva} Forskål, {\i Fl. Aegypt.} lxvi (1775) ({\i R. propinqua} R. Br.). Annual or biennial up to 20 cm. Leaf-lobes 5-15 on each side, entire. Pedicels 1-2·5 mm. Sepals 5, 2-2·5 mm; petals 5, 3-4·5 mm; dilation of claw indistinct or absent; lower petal retuse or shallowly bilobed. Capsule 4·5-7 × 4·5 mm, turbinate or elliptical, usually constricted below the prominent stigmatic lobes.{\i  Maritime sands. S. Spain} ({\b near Gibraltar}). Hs. ({\b N. Africa, S.W. Asia.})
