\pard\f0\fs28 Sect. RESEDA (Sect.{\i  Resedastrum} Duby). Leaves entire or pinnatifid. Sepals 6; petals 6, clawed, the two upper with limb 3-lobed; lateral lobes multifid or subentire; mid-lobe narrow, often indistinct; the two lateral petals similar, but with the lower lateral lobe absent or reduced; the two lower petals with the limb usually entire. Filaments usually caducous. Carpels 3.
\par

