\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 12. R. media} Lag.,{\i  Gen. Sp. Nov.} 17 (1816) ({\i R. macrosperma} Reichenb.). Like {\b 11} but many leaves with 1-4(-8) pairs of lobes and small terminal lobe; the entire leaves 30-50 × 4-8 mm; the intermediate and upper leaves more shortly cuneate or rounded at the base; bracts 1·5-2·5 mm; sepals finally 4-6 mm; upper petals with claw less incurved and limb sessile, digitate; capsule 13-16 × 6-8·5 mm, nodding. 2n = 12.{\i  Dry places. S.W. Europe.} *Az Bl Hs Lu.
